description: Fragment of a clay tablet, 15 lines of inscription. Neo-Assyrian.Fragment from the middle. Prescriptions and directions for ceremonies to be used for the benefit of sick people.
notes: fragment of a tablet with prescriptions against ašû, ṣibit ṭābti ('seizure of sweetness') and various hair-related problems, probably part of CRANIUM 4, CRANIUM 5 or SKIN
